  "response_text": "The teacher should approach the conversation with empathy, understanding, and a non-judgmental attitude. Here's a suggested script:\n\n\"Hello [Student's Name], I've noticed a change in your behavior lately, and I wanted to talk to you about it. I've observed that you seem less engaged in class and your usual cheerfulness seems to be missing. I'm here to help, and I want you to know that it's okay to share what's been on your mind.\n\nI'm not trying to pry, but I care about your well-being and I believe that discussing any issues you might be facing could help us find a solution together. If there's something bothering you, whether it's related to schoolwork or something else, please feel free to tell me. I'm here to listen and support you.\n\nRemember, there's no problem too big or too small. We can work through this together. Let's find a time when we can talk more privately, if you'd prefer. In the meantime, please know that I'm here for you.\"\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
